text.tspan: This is the third level overlay that can be reached when the user selects ‘View Payment History’ CTA from the Recipient
Details overlay. On this screen, the user can see a list of past payments to this recipient and their current status, along with
other pertinent details as seen here. The Recipients are ordered by creation date (the date which the payment was sent out
The subheader has the recipient name the payment history belongs to and their current status.
Here, a list of payments (excluding draft payments) made to this recipient can be seen with their current status. This
table is ordered by most recent creation date to oldest. The user can click into a line item to see more details.
Selecting a a line item will prompt an the Payment Details screen (see file DBBG_Payments_DD for more details).
Since this is the overlay experience, the ‘x’ icon will still be visible for users to action on. If the user clicks on the ‘x’
icon then it would be essentially like clicking on the icon on Recipient Landing overlay (first level overlay) which will
take the user back to the Payment Landing page.
The back button is to indicate that the user can go back to the previous step in the overlay experience, which in this
case, is the Recipient Details overlay.
